node_9.subject: Aika Shirosaki
node_9.description: This is Aika Shirosaki's plan for Monday February 13: Wake up and complete the morning routine at 7:00 am, Have breakfast and enjoy some quiet time at 7:30 am, Attend classes from 8:30 am to 12:00 pm, Have lunch with classmates at 12:00 pm, nervously discussing the new male student, Attend afternoon classes from 1:00 pm to 3:30 pm, Study in the library and gather courage to approach the new student from 3:30 pm to 5:00 pm, Have dinner around 5:00 pm, chatting with friends about their plans to get to know the boy, Join a study group for a class project from 6:00 pm to 7:00 pm, still feeling nervous but supported by friends, Go for a walk around campus to clear her mind at 7:00 pm, Join a social event where she can observe and possibly interact with the new student at 8:00 pm, Return to her dorm and unwind by reading a book at 9:30 pm, Prepare for bed, reflecting on her day and her feelings, at 10:30 pm, Lights out by 11:00 pm, hoping for the courage to reach out tomorrow..
